# Build the kill-test script and weekly drill

## Step

The fallback contract's eight-step scripted check (`design-fallback-contract.svx` §4), every assertion reading the stream and receipts, exit non-zero on any missing piece: kill the session → wait past TTL → `joelclaw notify send` an alert → assert `fallback.delivered` by flowId → assert platform receipt → restart → assert heartbeat returns → assert a fresh message gets an agent decision end-to-end.

Binds: real session kill, real DM, self-identified text (`⚠️ fallback: weekly kill-test drill <date>`). No drill flag, no test channel, no mock — a drill-aware fallback is a fallback with policy in it. The weekly ping is itself the receipt.

Resolved when the script passes against a live gateway + driver in rehearsal, the weekly schedule is wired through existing scheduling machinery (plus on-demand after any gateway deploy), and the cutover sitting can run it as probe (c).

## Result (2026-07-21)

Closed as code-complete and ready for the supervised cutover sitting. The real gateway session does not exist yet, so no pane was killed, no real DM was sent, the production heartbeat key was untouched, and the weekly schedule remains unarmed.

Delivered:

- `packages/agent-comms-driver/src/kill-test.ts` — an XState lifecycle that runs the fallback contract's eight assertions in order. Stream replay proves `fallback.delivered` and the recovery decision by `flowId`. ClickHouse journal readback proves the confirmed platform receipt and exact text `⚠️ fallback: weekly kill-test drill <date>`. Any missing evidence exits non-zero.
- `packages/agent-comms-driver/src/kill-test-live.ts` — injectable live adapters for Herdr pane closure, Redis heartbeat existence, `joelclaw notify send`, stream trace, journal trace, wake-registry restart, receipt persistence, and weekly schedule admission.
- `packages/agent-comms-driver/scripts/kill-test.ts` — refuses to run without `--confirm-live-gateway-kill`; the package's `kill-drill` command supplies that confirmation for the supervised sitting. A post-stop failure requests an emergency successor before returning non-zero.
- `packages/agent-comms-driver/scripts/arm-weekly-kill-drill.ts` plus `.brain/tasks/agent-comms-gateway-weekly-kill-drill.svx` — ready-but-unarmed weekly recurrence through the existing wake registry. The arm path checks for an existing marked schedule, verifies new admission by readback, and cancels plus verifies removal when readback fails.
- `packages/agent-comms-driver/__tests__/kill-test.test.ts` — deterministic injected-seam coverage for all eight assertions, missing evidence, emergency restart, exact drill text, receipt directory creation, schedule idempotency, cancellation, and cancellation readback.

One-command arm step, only after the supervised live drill passes:

```sh
pnpm --filter @joelclaw/agent-comms-driver arm-weekly-drill
```

